725
00:54:48,284 --> 00:54:52,675
The most significant discovery
in the history...

726
00:54:52,844 --> 00:54:54,914
...of mankind. Oh, I know.

727
00:54:57,644 --> 00:54:59,396
It's incredible, it really is.

728
00:54:59,564 --> 00:55:03,239
But I wanted to talk to them.

729
00:55:03,564 --> 00:55:06,283
I mean, don't you want to know
why they came?

730
00:55:07,604 --> 00:55:09,083
Why they abandoned us?

731
00:55:09,484 --> 00:55:11,236
I just want answers, baby.

732
00:55:11,404 --> 00:55:12,803
We were right, Charlie.

733
00:55:13,244 --> 00:55:15,235
I have proof.

734
00:55:17,164 --> 00:55:18,040
Look.

735
00:55:23,764 --> 00:55:26,756
Their genetic material predates ours.

736
00:55:26,924 --> 00:55:28,357
We come from them.

737
00:55:29,764 --> 00:55:31,356
- You're kidding me.
- No.

738
00:55:34,244 --> 00:55:35,393
Okay.

739
00:55:35,884 --> 00:55:36,999
Okay.

740
00:55:37,964 --> 00:55:41,957
Okay. I guess you can take
your father's cross off now.

741
00:55:42,684 --> 00:55:44,834
Why would I want to do that?

742
00:55:45,324 --> 00:55:46,996
Because they made us.

743
00:55:47,164 --> 00:55:48,392
And who made them?

744
00:55:49,284 --> 00:55:51,240
Well, exactly. We'll never know.

745
00:55:51,404 --> 00:55:53,395
But here's what we do know:

746
00:55:53,564 --> 00:55:57,239
That there is nothing special
about the creation of life.

747
00:55:57,404 --> 00:55:58,757
Right? Anybody can do it.

748
00:55:58,924 --> 00:56:01,802
All you need is a dash of DNA
and half a brain, right?

749
00:56:04,684 --> 00:56:05,833
I can't.

750
00:56:07,364 --> 00:56:09,514
I can't create life.

751
00:56:11,284 --> 00:56:13,844
What does that say about me?

752
00:56:15,084 --> 00:56:17,962
Ellie, that's not-- I didn't mean--

