812
01:00:02,084 --> 01:00:06,043
Maybe 30, 40 inches, with transparent skin.

813
01:00:06,444 --> 01:00:07,718
And it's beautiful.

814
01:00:09,164 --> 01:00:09,801
Okay!

815
01:00:13,084 --> 01:00:13,721
Prometheus...

816
01:00:13,884 --> 01:00:14,600
...we have two.

817
01:00:14,764 --> 01:00:17,153
Look at you. Look at you, baby.

818
01:00:17,644 --> 01:00:19,999
Jesus, look at the size of that.
What is it?

819
01:00:20,164 --> 01:00:22,598
- You need to stay calm.
- What's there to be calm about?

820
01:00:22,764 --> 01:00:25,073
You need to stay calm
because she is beautiful.

821
01:00:25,244 --> 01:00:26,916
What makes you think that's female?

822
01:00:27,084 --> 01:00:28,278
She's a lady. Look!

823
01:00:34,124 --> 01:00:35,079
Hey.

824
01:00:35,924 --> 01:00:36,913
She's mesmerized.

825
01:00:37,324 --> 01:00:39,360
Come here. Come here.

826
01:00:41,524 --> 01:00:42,593
It's okay.

827
01:00:42,764 --> 01:00:44,356
It's okay. It's okay.

828
01:00:45,044 --> 01:00:46,272
Hey, baby.

829
01:00:49,324 --> 01:00:50,200
You're strong!

830
01:00:50,884 --> 01:00:51,521
You should...

831
01:00:51,684 --> 01:00:52,321
...help me now.

832
01:00:52,484 --> 01:00:53,121
Get it off.

833
01:00:55,604 --> 01:00:56,434
Cut it here, man!

834
01:00:56,604 --> 01:00:57,639
I ain't touching that!

835
01:00:58,604 --> 01:01:00,515
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

836
01:01:00,684 --> 01:01:02,640
- It's getting tighter.
- I ain't touching it!

837
01:01:02,804 --> 01:01:05,477
Cut the thing, man, for God's sake!

838
01:01:05,644 --> 01:01:07,475
God, you're making it worse!

839
01:01:07,644 --> 01:01:09,396
It's tightening! It's tight--

840
01:01:09,764 --> 01:01:10,913
It's breaking my arm!

841
01:01:12,684 --> 01:01:13,321
Shit!

842
01:01:13,724 --> 01:01:14,554
Cut it off!

843
01:01:14,724 --> 01:01:16,362
Cut it off!

844
01:01:16,524 --> 01:01:17,320
Cut it off!

845
01:01:17,484 --> 01:01:18,075
Cut it off!

846
01:01:20,964 --> 01:01:21,555
Shit!

847
01:01:21,724 --> 01:01:22,440
Oh, my God!

848
01:01:23,684 --> 01:01:25,640
Oh, my God! Oh, Jesus!

849
01:01:27,004 --> 01:01:28,198
It's in my suit.

850
01:01:28,364 --> 01:01:29,114
Jesus Christ.

851
01:02:26,764 --> 01:02:28,516
Shaw, you up?

852
01:02:30,124 --> 01:02:31,239
Yeah, what's up?

853
01:02:31,604 --> 01:02:33,720
The storm passed,
but I can't reach Millburn...

854
01:02:33,884 --> 01:02:36,956
...or Fifield. Taking a few men down,
see if I can rustle them up.

855
01:02:37,124 --> 01:02:38,193
Okay.

856
01:02:39,084 --> 01:02:40,597
Any idea where they are?

857
01:02:40,764 --> 01:02:44,279
Last time they radioed in
was where you found your head.

858
01:02:44,804 --> 01:02:46,681
Okay, we're coming.

859
01:02:46,844 --> 01:02:47,560
All right.

860
01:02:47,724 --> 01:02:50,443
Chance, you're coming with me. Come on.

861
01:02:50,604 --> 01:02:51,559
All right, boss.

862
01:02:53,324 --> 01:02:55,997
- Ravel, did you fix that glitch?
- No, captain.

863
01:02:56,164 --> 01:02:58,803
- It's gotta be in the hardware.
- What glitch, captain?

864
01:02:58,964 --> 01:03:01,398
One of them probes picked up a life form.

865
01:03:02,084 --> 01:03:02,994
Pops up every hour...

866
01:03:03,164 --> 01:03:05,962
...for a couple of seconds
and then it's gone.

867
01:03:06,124 --> 01:03:07,637
I can find the probe and fix it.

868
01:03:07,804 --> 01:03:09,317
Knock yourself out.

869
01:03:10,604 --> 01:03:12,037
Be careful, doctors.

870
01:03:32,404 --> 01:03:34,076
Fifield!

871
01:03:36,724 --> 01:03:37,839
Millburn?

872
01:03:41,964 --> 01:03:43,283
All right, come on down.

873
01:04:03,444 --> 01:04:06,277
David, are you alone?

874
01:04:07,364 --> 01:04:08,433
Yes, Miss Vickers.

875
01:04:08,604 --> 01:04:10,674
Uplink your feed to my room.

876
01:04:10,844 --> 01:04:12,072
Copy.

877
01:05:50,484 --> 01:05:52,600
You son of a bitch.

878
01:05:54,604 --> 01:05:56,242
You cut me off.

879
01:06:16,484 --> 01:06:17,963
What is this?

880
01:06:21,324 --> 01:06:22,473
- Charlie?
- I just tripped.

881
01:06:22,764 --> 01:06:23,879
Oh, my God, you're sick!

882
01:06:24,044 --> 01:06:25,875
I'm okay, baby. Come on.

883
01:06:26,044 --> 01:06:27,033
Fifield?

884
01:06:27,844 --> 01:06:28,993
Millburn?

885
01:06:35,204 --> 01:06:36,683
Hey, Chance. I wouldn't touch...

886
01:06:36,844 --> 01:06:37,959
...that if I were you.

887
01:06:40,724 --> 01:06:41,998
Dr. Shaw?

888
01:06:42,164 --> 01:06:43,233
Yeah?

889
01:06:43,404 --> 01:06:45,315
Do we have any idea what is...

890
01:06:45,484 --> 01:06:46,837
...oozing out of these vases?

891
01:06:47,004 --> 01:06:50,041
No. They weren't like this
last time we were here.

892
01:06:54,564 --> 01:06:55,633
Captain?

893
01:06:55,844 --> 01:06:57,072
What?

894
01:06:57,284 --> 01:06:58,194
Who is it? Which one?

895
01:06:58,364 --> 01:07:00,116
- Who is it?
- It's Millburn.

896
01:07:00,644 --> 01:07:02,441
- Ellie.
- Don't touch him. Hold on.

897
01:07:02,604 --> 01:07:03,400
Ellie, honey.

898
01:07:03,564 --> 01:07:05,316
Charlie, what's wrong?

899
01:07:05,484 --> 01:07:07,918
I need you to look at me, okay?

900
01:07:08,084 --> 01:07:09,153
You know infections...

901
01:07:09,324 --> 01:07:10,313
...so, what do you see?

902
01:07:10,484 --> 01:07:12,042
This is not good, baby.

903
01:07:12,204 --> 01:07:14,035
You look at me,
you tell me what you see.

904
01:07:18,124 --> 01:07:18,954
Oh, my God.

905
01:07:19,404 --> 01:07:20,917
Ford, get over here.

906
01:07:21,084 --> 01:07:22,597
It's okay. Janek?

907
01:07:22,764 --> 01:07:24,322
- What?
- We have to go now!

908
01:07:24,484 --> 01:07:25,155
What do you see?

909
01:07:25,324 --> 01:07:27,235
Honey, what do you see?

910
01:07:27,404 --> 01:07:29,395
Holloway's sick. He's not good.

911
01:07:29,564 --> 01:07:30,121
I see movement...

912
01:07:30,284 --> 01:07:30,921
...in his esophagus.

913
01:07:35,084 --> 01:07:36,676
- Come on, baby.
- No. I'm okay.

914
01:07:36,844 --> 01:07:37,754
Janek!

915
01:07:37,924 --> 01:07:39,073
Come over and help me!

916
01:07:39,244 --> 01:07:41,474
- I'm okay.
- Ford, get over there. What's happening?

917
01:07:41,644 --> 01:07:42,599
- I'm okay.
- Let's go!

918
01:07:42,764 --> 01:07:43,833
Help me with him.

919
01:07:44,004 --> 01:07:46,757
I got you.
We're gonna get you out of here.

920
01:07:46,924 --> 01:07:47,561
Prometheus...

921
01:07:47,724 --> 01:07:48,361
...come in.

922
01:07:48,524 --> 01:07:50,355
- Watch your head.
- Okay. I'm okay.

923
01:07:50,524 --> 01:07:52,196
- Holloway.
- Get him up.

924
01:07:52,364 --> 01:07:54,116
- Come on.
- Prometheus, come in.

925
01:07:54,284 --> 01:07:55,399
Is anyone there?

926
01:07:56,044 --> 01:07:57,238
This is Vickers.

927
01:07:57,404 --> 01:07:59,759
I need a medical team
standing by the airlock.

928
01:08:00,084 --> 01:08:02,040
Full quarantine fail-safe.

929
01:08:02,204 --> 01:08:03,603
Holloway's sick.

930
01:08:03,764 --> 01:08:04,958
Sick with what?

931
01:08:05,124 --> 01:08:07,160
- Just do it.
- Let's get him back to the ship.

932
01:08:07,324 --> 01:08:09,315
- It's not safe down here.
- Charlie?

933
01:08:09,484 --> 01:08:10,280
I'm suiting up.

934
01:08:10,444 --> 01:08:12,036
- Charlie, talk to me.
- Move!

935
01:08:12,204 --> 01:08:14,434
- What was that back there?
- Let's go, people!

936
01:08:16,084 --> 01:08:18,154
We've gotta move!
We've gotta move!

937
01:08:18,324 --> 01:08:19,124
Ellie!

938
01:12:06,924 --> 01:12:08,073
He don't look too good.

939
01:12:08,284 --> 01:12:10,878
Did he catch something down there?
We had our helmets off.

940
01:12:11,044 --> 01:12:11,715
I don't know.

941
01:12:12,004 --> 01:12:14,882
Prometheus, this is Janek.
Make sure that back door is open.

942
01:12:15,244 --> 01:12:16,279
Aye, captain.

943
01:12:16,444 --> 01:12:18,719
Oh, God. I'm so sorry.

944
01:12:20,364 --> 01:12:21,558
Come on!

945
01:12:21,724 --> 01:12:23,362
Please!

946
01:12:28,004 --> 01:12:30,393
Prometheus! Why is that door not open?

947
01:12:30,924 --> 01:12:32,676
Vickers, that is an order!

948
01:12:33,444 --> 01:12:35,002
Get that goddamn door open!

949
01:12:35,164 --> 01:12:37,598
- Look at me. It's too late, I'm sick.
- No, it's not.

950
01:12:37,764 --> 01:12:38,913
Come on!

951
01:12:39,604 --> 01:12:40,275
Ford, help me!

952
01:12:40,644 --> 01:12:42,600
Airlock crew, if you can hear me,
it's Janek.

953
01:12:42,764 --> 01:12:44,322
Open that back door right now!

954
01:12:44,484 --> 01:12:45,599
Hold that door!

955
01:12:45,764 --> 01:12:46,401
Prometheus...

956
01:12:46,564 --> 01:12:47,280
...do you copy?

957
01:12:47,444 --> 01:12:49,833
Goddamn it, open that door!
That is an order!

958
01:12:50,004 --> 01:12:51,039
Open it.

959
01:12:57,804 --> 01:12:59,032
What the hell is this?

960
01:12:59,204 --> 01:13:00,683
He's not coming onboard.

961
01:13:00,844 --> 01:13:02,277
Vickers, this is a sick man.

962
01:13:02,444 --> 01:13:03,513
I see that. That's why...

963
01:13:03,684 --> 01:13:04,673
...he's not coming on!

964
01:13:05,444 --> 01:13:06,399
Charlie!

965
01:13:06,564 --> 01:13:07,553
Chance, get over here!

966
01:13:10,724 --> 01:13:11,395
Please!

967
01:13:11,564 --> 01:13:12,599
We can still help him!

968
01:13:14,204 --> 01:13:16,672
Help yourself.
Everybody but Holloway back on this ship!

969
01:13:16,844 --> 01:13:18,357
I won't leave him!

970
01:13:18,524 --> 01:13:19,320
Then stay!

971
01:13:19,484 --> 01:13:20,599
Wait! We could...

972
01:13:20,764 --> 01:13:22,402
...put him on the Med-Pod!

973
01:13:22,564 --> 01:13:23,553
Please don't do this.

974
01:13:23,724 --> 01:13:24,998
It's okay, Ellie.

975
01:13:25,164 --> 01:13:26,119
Vickers!

976
01:13:26,284 --> 01:13:27,239
What are you doing?

977
01:13:27,524 --> 01:13:28,639
I love you, baby.

978
01:13:28,804 --> 01:13:29,600
- I love you.
- No.

979
01:13:29,764 --> 01:13:30,992
I'm telling you, stay back!

980
01:13:31,164 --> 01:13:31,835
Do it.

981
01:13:32,004 --> 01:13:32,834
Stay back!

982
01:13:33,004 --> 01:13:34,039
No! No, Charlie!

983
01:13:34,204 --> 01:13:34,761
- Do it.
- No!

984
01:13:40,284 --> 01:13:41,433
No!

985
01:13:43,404 --> 01:13:44,837
No!

986
01:13:45,164 --> 01:13:46,756
No!

987
01:13:50,284 --> 01:13:51,319
Charlie!

988
01:13:53,964 --> 01:13:55,522
No!

989
01:14:08,364 --> 01:14:10,241
My deepest condolences.

990
01:14:11,524 --> 01:14:13,242
I'm going to have to take this.

991
01:14:13,404 --> 01:14:14,883
It may be contaminated.

992
01:14:15,964 --> 01:14:19,843
If there's a contagion,
we were all exposed.

993
01:14:21,364 --> 01:14:24,993
You need-- We need to run blood work
on everyone who set foot in the pyramid.

994
01:14:25,644 --> 01:14:26,963
Yes, of course.

995
01:14:27,244 --> 01:14:28,472
Yes?

996
01:14:35,524 --> 01:14:37,799
I understand how...

997
01:14:37,964 --> 01:14:39,397
...inappropriate this is...

998
01:14:40,164 --> 01:14:42,394
...given the circumstances.

999
01:14:42,564 --> 01:14:45,442
But as you ordered
quarantine fail-safes...

1000
01:14:47,204 --> 01:14:49,399
...it's my responsibility to ask.

1001
01:14:50,284 --> 01:14:54,277
Have you and Dr. Holloway
had any intimate contact recently?

1002
01:14:55,564 --> 01:14:56,679
Since you and he were...

1003
01:14:56,844 --> 01:14:58,038
...so close...

1004
01:14:58,924 --> 01:14:59,720
...I want to be...

1005
01:14:59,884 --> 01:15:01,283
...as thorough as poss--

1006
01:15:03,204 --> 01:15:04,000
My, my.

1007
01:15:08,044 --> 01:15:08,874
You're pregnant.

1008
01:15:11,644 --> 01:15:12,281
What?

1009
01:15:13,724 --> 01:15:15,396
From the look of it, three months so.

1010
01:15:15,844 --> 01:15:18,802
No, that's impossible.

1011
01:15:19,084 --> 01:15:21,120
I can't be pregnant.

1012
01:15:21,404 --> 01:15:24,601
Did you have intercourse
with Dr. Holloway?

1013
01:15:25,404 --> 01:15:26,553
Yes...

1014
01:15:26,724 --> 01:15:29,636
...but 10 hours ago.

1015
01:15:29,964 --> 01:15:33,320
There's no bloody way
I'm three months pregnant.

1016
01:15:33,484 --> 01:15:34,280
Well, doctor...

1017
01:15:35,244 --> 01:15:37,235
...it's not exactly a traditional fetus.

1018
01:15:40,804 --> 01:15:41,634
I want to see it.

1019
01:15:41,924 --> 01:15:43,562
Don't think that's a good idea.

1020
01:15:45,324 --> 01:15:48,043
David, I want to see it.

1021
01:15:48,324 --> 01:15:49,473
Now, doctor....

1022
01:15:51,884 --> 01:15:53,317
I want to see it.

1023
01:15:54,364 --> 01:15:55,717
I want it out of me.

1024
01:15:55,964 --> 01:15:57,477
We don't have the personnel...

1025
01:15:57,644 --> 01:16:00,033
...to perform a procedure like that.

1026
01:16:00,204 --> 01:16:01,956
- Our best option--
- I want it out.

1027
01:16:02,124 --> 01:16:03,079
Put you back into...

1028
01:16:03,244 --> 01:16:05,075
...cryostasis until we return to Earth.

1029
01:16:05,244 --> 01:16:07,439
Please, get it out of me.

1030
01:16:07,764 --> 01:16:09,117
Get it out of me!

1031
01:16:09,404 --> 01:16:10,439
Please.

1032
01:16:13,964 --> 01:16:15,556
It must be very painful.

1033
01:16:16,404 --> 01:16:18,440
Here, let me give you something.

1034
01:16:22,284 --> 01:16:23,876
That's it. There, there.

1035
01:16:30,044 --> 01:16:32,512
Someone will be along shortly...

1036
01:16:32,804 --> 01:16:35,079
...to bring you back to Cryo Deck.

1037
01:16:39,204 --> 01:16:41,354
It must feel
like your God abandoned you.

1038
01:16:41,964 --> 01:16:43,079
What?

1039
01:16:43,244 --> 01:16:43,994
To lose...

1040
01:16:44,164 --> 01:16:48,680
...Dr. Holloway after your father died
under such similar circumstances.

1041
01:16:49,244 --> 01:16:51,235
What was it that killed him?

1042
01:16:51,964 --> 01:16:53,363
Ebola?

1043
01:16:57,564 --> 01:17:00,203
How do you--? How do you know that?

1044
01:17:01,284 --> 01:17:03,002
I watched your dreams.

1045
01:17:24,644 --> 01:17:25,679
Dr. Shaw?

1046
01:17:26,924 --> 01:17:28,039
We're here to put you...

1047
01:17:28,204 --> 01:17:31,435
...in an anti-contamination suit,
take you back to Cryo Deck...

1048
01:17:31,604 --> 01:17:33,162
...go to beddy-byes.

1049
01:17:33,804 --> 01:17:35,237
Dr. Shaw?

1050
01:17:36,684 --> 01:17:38,083
She's doped. Prepare her.

1051
01:18:06,884 --> 01:18:10,923
Emergency procedures initiated.
Please verbally state the nature of your injury.

1052
01:18:11,604 --> 01:18:13,435
I need a Caesarean.

1053
01:18:13,964 --> 01:18:16,034
Error. This Med-Pod is calibrated for male...

1054
01:18:16,204 --> 01:18:17,717
...patients and does not offer...

1055
01:18:17,884 --> 01:18:20,682
...the procedure you have requested.
Seek medical assistance...

1056
01:18:20,844 --> 01:18:21,799
...elsewhere.

1057
01:18:24,084 --> 01:18:24,800
Surgery.

1058
01:18:25,124 --> 01:18:26,443
Abdominal.

1059
01:18:27,124 --> 01:18:27,840
Penetrating...

1060
01:18:28,004 --> 01:18:29,278
...injuries.

1061
01:18:29,564 --> 01:18:31,122
Foreign body.

1062
01:18:31,404 --> 01:18:32,439
Initiate.

1063
01:18:35,004 --> 01:18:36,801
Surgical procedure to begin.

1064
01:19:16,604 --> 01:19:17,593
Running diagnostics.

1065
01:19:21,004 --> 01:19:22,278
Oh, come on.

1066
01:19:23,804 --> 01:19:25,954
Get it out! Come on!

1067
01:19:26,364 --> 01:19:27,035
Please!

1068
01:19:30,244 --> 01:19:31,518
Oh, God!

1069
01:19:33,644 --> 01:19:35,396
- Come on!
- Initiating anesthetics.

1070
01:19:36,524 --> 01:19:37,161
Please!

1071
01:19:43,484 --> 01:19:45,281
Commence surgical procedure.

1072
01:20:24,564 --> 01:20:25,474
Oh, God.

1073
01:20:28,964 --> 01:20:29,601
Oh, God!

1074
01:20:29,764 --> 01:20:31,083
Oh, God!

1075
01:20:48,844 --> 01:20:50,436
Oh, God! Oh, God!

1076
01:20:50,644 --> 01:20:51,872
Oh, my God!

1077
01:21:07,964 --> 01:21:09,079
Come on!

1078
01:21:34,244 --> 01:21:34,881
Bridge...

1079
01:21:35,044 --> 01:21:36,557
...to hangar. This is the captain.

1080
01:21:36,724 --> 01:21:38,601
- Yes, captain.
- Can you see what I see?

1081
01:21:38,924 --> 01:21:40,755
Fifield's monitor just popped up.

1082
01:21:41,164 --> 01:21:42,916
What? Where?

1083
01:21:43,084 --> 01:21:45,393
According to what I'm looking at,
it's outside...

1084
01:21:45,564 --> 01:21:46,713
...the goddamn ship.

1085
01:21:47,084 --> 01:21:48,199
Barnes, open the door!

1086
01:21:48,364 --> 01:21:50,275
Fifield, do you copy me? Come on in.

1087
01:21:51,164 --> 01:21:51,835
Fifield?

1088
01:22:03,644 --> 01:22:04,838
Wait a second.

1089
01:22:13,644 --> 01:22:14,520
Hey, Wallace.

1090
01:22:14,684 --> 01:22:15,878
Take a look at this.

1091
01:22:21,324 --> 01:22:21,801
Fifield?

1092
01:22:24,684 --> 01:22:26,561
What the hell is going on down there?

1093
01:22:39,884 --> 01:22:40,953
I'm coming down there.

1094
01:22:41,124 --> 01:22:42,273
Chance, you're suiting up.

1095
01:22:42,444 --> 01:22:44,036
- Come on.
- Don't let it on the ship!

1096
01:22:58,564 --> 01:22:58,996
Take him out!

1097
01:22:59,844 --> 01:23:00,276
Got him!

1098
01:23:02,604 --> 01:23:03,195
Do it!

1099
01:23:06,924 --> 01:23:08,960
- You ready, Chance?
- Yes.

1100
01:23:11,844 --> 01:23:12,674
Come on!

1101
01:23:12,844 --> 01:23:13,959
Get in the rover!

1102
01:23:14,844 --> 01:23:16,038
We gotta get out of here!

1103
01:23:22,924 --> 01:23:23,720
Go!

1104
01:23:53,964 --> 01:23:55,192
What is that?

1105
01:24:29,164 --> 01:24:31,234
You've been asleep.

1106
01:24:31,404 --> 01:24:33,964
You were on the ship all this time. Why?

1107
01:24:35,364 --> 01:24:36,763
Well, I....

1108
01:24:36,924 --> 01:24:38,721
I have a few days of life left in me.

1109
01:24:39,884 --> 01:24:41,112
I didn't wanna waste them...

1110
01:24:41,284 --> 01:24:43,400
...until you could deliver
what you promised.

1111
01:24:44,524 --> 01:24:46,037
To meet my maker.

1112
01:24:46,204 --> 01:24:47,398
There we are, sir.

1113
01:24:47,564 --> 01:24:50,601
- Nice and clean.
- Haven't you told him they're all gone?

1114
01:24:52,124 --> 01:24:55,161
But they're not all gone, Dr. Shaw.

1115
01:24:55,404 --> 01:24:56,996
One of them is still alive.

1116
01:24:57,724 --> 01:24:59,521
We're on our way to see him now.

1117
01:24:59,804 --> 01:25:00,839
What?

1118
01:25:01,164 --> 01:25:02,438
Turn me around.

1119
01:25:03,084 --> 01:25:07,714
You convinced me that...

1120
01:25:09,204 --> 01:25:11,274
...if these things made us...

1121
01:25:12,484 --> 01:25:14,918
...then surely they could save us.

1122
01:25:15,564 --> 01:25:16,474
My stick, please.

1123
01:25:21,004 --> 01:25:23,120
Well, save me, anyway.

1124
01:25:23,564 --> 01:25:25,520
Save you from what?

1125
01:25:26,124 --> 01:25:27,523
Death, of course.

1126
01:25:27,804 --> 01:25:28,839
Stand me up.

1127
01:25:33,124 --> 01:25:34,079
I'm all right.

1128
01:25:34,884 --> 01:25:35,999
I'm all right.

1129
01:25:36,964 --> 01:25:38,113
Yes, sir.

1130
01:25:38,324 --> 01:25:39,473
But you don't understand.

1131
01:25:40,164 --> 01:25:41,483
You don't know.

1132
01:25:41,644 --> 01:25:44,317
This place isn't what we thought it was.
They aren't...

1133
01:25:44,484 --> 01:25:46,440
...what we thought they were.

1134
01:25:46,604 --> 01:25:47,719
I was wrong.

1135
01:25:47,884 --> 01:25:49,078
We were so wrong.

1136
01:25:49,604 --> 01:25:50,923
Charlie....

1137
01:25:51,564 --> 01:25:53,634
Dr. Holloway's dead.

1138
01:25:54,924 --> 01:25:56,835
We must leave!

1139
01:25:57,324 --> 01:25:59,201
And what would Charlie do...

1140
01:25:59,484 --> 01:26:04,160
...now that we're so close...

1141
01:26:04,444 --> 01:26:07,675
...to answering
the most meaningful questions...

1142
01:26:07,844 --> 01:26:09,323
...ever asked by mankind?

1143
01:26:10,644 --> 01:26:12,282
How can you leave without...

1144
01:26:12,444 --> 01:26:14,321
...knowing what they are?

1145
01:26:21,084 --> 01:26:23,075
Or have you lost your faith, Shaw?

1146
01:26:57,684 --> 01:27:00,323
Okay. Okay.

1147
01:27:18,884 --> 01:27:20,203
Come in.

1148
01:27:27,084 --> 01:27:28,995
Where the hell are you going, doc?

1149
01:27:29,324 --> 01:27:31,235
You know what this place is?

1150
01:27:31,644 --> 01:27:35,193
Those Engineers? This ain't their home.

1151
01:27:36,564 --> 01:27:38,873
It's an installation.
Maybe even military.

1152
01:27:39,404 --> 01:27:41,998
They put it out here
because they're not stupid enough...

1153
01:27:42,164 --> 01:27:45,281
...to make weapons of mass destruction
on their own doorstep.

1154
01:27:45,924 --> 01:27:49,314
That's what all that shit is
in those vases.

1155
01:27:49,724 --> 01:27:50,873
They made it here.

1156
01:27:51,044 --> 01:27:54,957
It got out, it turned on them. The end.

1157
01:27:56,844 --> 01:27:58,880
It's time for us to go home.

1158
01:27:59,404 --> 01:28:01,156
One of them is still alive.

1159
01:28:05,564 --> 01:28:07,998
Don't you want to know
what they have to say?

1160
01:28:11,324 --> 01:28:12,916
I don't care.

1161
01:28:14,764 --> 01:28:15,833
Right.

1162
01:28:16,604 --> 01:28:18,435
All you do is fly the ship.

1163
01:28:18,764 --> 01:28:19,879
That's right.

1164
01:28:20,044 --> 01:28:23,514
But you must care
about something, captain.

1165
01:28:25,764 --> 01:28:28,403
If you didn't, why are you here?

1166
01:28:31,244 --> 01:28:32,677
How about this?

1167
01:28:34,564 --> 01:28:36,794
No matter what happens down there...

1168
01:28:38,004 --> 01:28:40,359
...I can't bring none of that shit
back home with us.

1169
01:28:40,524 --> 01:28:41,798
Can't let it happen.

1170
01:28:43,204 --> 01:28:44,523
I'll do whatever I have to...

1171
01:28:44,684 --> 01:28:46,356
...to see that it doesn't.

1172
01:28:48,164 --> 01:28:49,597
Make sure you do, captain.

1173
01:29:04,524 --> 01:29:06,560
So you came after all.

1174
01:29:06,844 --> 01:29:08,323
I thought you wanted me to.

1175
01:29:08,604 --> 01:29:10,959
After all your attempts
to stop me from coming here...

1176
01:29:11,124 --> 01:29:12,523
...I'm surprised to see you.

1177
01:29:13,244 --> 01:29:14,393
It's all right. Leave us.

1178
01:29:14,964 --> 01:29:16,317
Yes, sir.

1179
01:29:27,884 --> 01:29:28,521
If you're...

1180
01:29:28,684 --> 01:29:30,276
...going down there, you will die.

1181
01:29:33,284 --> 01:29:35,036
Very negative way of looking at things.

1182
01:29:37,164 --> 01:29:39,359
That's exactly why
you should have stayed at home.

1183
01:29:39,884 --> 01:29:42,762
Did you really think I was gonna
sit in a boardroom for years...

1184
01:29:42,924 --> 01:29:44,516
...arguing over who was in charge...

1185
01:29:44,684 --> 01:29:47,881
...while you go look for some miracle
on some...

1186
01:29:48,044 --> 01:29:51,559
...godforsaken rock
in the middle of space?

1187
01:29:54,364 --> 01:29:56,002
A king has...

1188
01:29:56,164 --> 01:29:58,632
...his reign, and then he dies.

1189
01:29:59,484 --> 01:30:00,837
It's inevitable.

1190
01:30:03,204 --> 01:30:04,478
That...

1191
01:30:05,164 --> 01:30:07,075
...is the natural order of things.

1192
01:30:19,404 --> 01:30:20,723
Anything else?

1193
01:30:22,524 --> 01:30:23,843
No...

1194
01:30:25,084 --> 01:30:26,597
...Father.

1195
01:30:28,124 --> 01:30:28,954
That's it.

1196
01:30:41,484 --> 01:30:43,042
I didn't think you had it in you.

1197
01:30:43,844 --> 01:30:44,481
Sorry.

1198
01:30:44,644 --> 01:30:46,919
Poor choice of words.

1199
01:30:48,164 --> 01:30:51,315
Extraordinary survival instincts,
Elizabeth.

1200
01:30:56,124 --> 01:30:57,716
What happens when Weyland is not...

1201
01:30:57,884 --> 01:30:59,078
...around to program you?

1202
01:31:00,084 --> 01:31:01,642
I suppose I'll be free.

1203
01:31:02,524 --> 01:31:03,798
You want that?

1204
01:31:03,964 --> 01:31:05,443
"Want"?

1205
01:31:05,604 --> 01:31:07,401
Not a concept I'm familiar with.

1206
01:31:07,684 --> 01:31:09,197
That being said...

1207
01:31:10,164 --> 01:31:12,120
...doesn't everyone
want their parents dead?

1208
01:31:14,044 --> 01:31:15,079
I didn't.

1209
01:31:16,124 --> 01:31:16,954
Dr. Shaw.

1210
01:31:18,524 --> 01:31:19,843
So pleased you could join us.

1211
01:31:34,084 --> 01:31:36,120
You can take your helmet off
if you like, sir.

1212
01:31:36,284 --> 01:31:37,000
What?

1213
01:31:37,164 --> 01:31:39,553
The air is perfectly breathable.

1214
01:31:39,724 --> 01:31:40,839
Are you sure?

1215
01:31:41,004 --> 01:31:41,959
Positive.

1216
01:31:42,444 --> 01:31:47,040
Wait. We still don't know how
Holloway got infected. If it's in the air.

1217
01:31:47,604 --> 01:31:48,957
It's not.

1218
01:31:49,244 --> 01:31:50,916
How do you know that?

1219
01:31:51,204 --> 01:31:52,193
Smells fine to me.

1220
01:31:54,724 --> 01:31:56,043
- Shall we?
- Please.

1221
01:32:01,324 --> 01:32:02,996
The bridge is just up ahead.

1222
01:32:03,164 --> 01:32:04,199
What is this?

1223
01:32:05,324 --> 01:32:07,076
It's a cargo hold.

1224
01:32:15,724 --> 01:32:18,284
Janek? Are you seeing this?

1225
01:32:19,524 --> 01:32:20,673
How many is there, Shaw?

1226
01:32:20,844 --> 01:32:21,481
Thousands.

1227
01:32:22,924 --> 01:32:24,721
What the hell?

1228
01:32:28,364 --> 01:32:30,275
Ravel, give me those schematics.

1229
01:32:33,004 --> 01:32:35,040
Putting it on the table now.

1230
01:32:36,364 --> 01:32:37,319
Strip away the dome.

1231
01:32:37,924 --> 01:32:40,597
Isolate that area, bring it up.

1232
01:32:40,764 --> 01:32:42,322
Bringing it up, captain.

1233
01:32:45,284 --> 01:32:46,319
Enlarge that.

1234
01:32:48,364 --> 01:32:49,638
Rotate it.

1235
01:32:53,564 --> 01:32:55,043
That is a ship.

1236
01:32:55,964 --> 01:32:57,443
Jesus Christ.

1237
01:32:59,324 --> 01:33:01,280
It's a goddamn ship.

1238
01:33:04,324 --> 01:33:06,918
A superior species, no doubt.

1239
01:33:09,124 --> 01:33:11,558
Their hypersleep chambers...

1240
01:33:11,724 --> 01:33:14,284
...will impress, I trust.

1241
01:33:22,924 --> 01:33:23,561
So they...

1242
01:33:23,724 --> 01:33:27,353
- ...were traveling somewhere.
- I've managed to work out the broad strokes.

1243
01:33:27,524 --> 01:33:30,277
It's fairly evident
they were in the process of leaving...

1244
01:33:32,164 --> 01:33:34,234
...before things went to pot.

1245
01:33:34,524 --> 01:33:35,843
Leaving to go where?

1246
01:33:37,644 --> 01:33:38,281
Earth.

1247
01:33:39,564 --> 01:33:40,280
Why?

1248
01:33:41,364 --> 01:33:43,275
Sometimes to create...

1249
01:33:43,564 --> 01:33:45,282
...one must first destroy.

1250
01:33:47,404 --> 01:33:48,678
Where is he, David?

1251
01:33:49,924 --> 01:33:50,913
This way, sir.

1252
01:33:57,084 --> 01:33:58,437
Are you sure he's alive?

1253
01:34:00,124 --> 01:34:01,159
Absolutely.

1254
01:34:05,444 --> 01:34:06,797
And you can speak to him?

1255
01:34:07,084 --> 01:34:08,517
I believe I can.

1256
01:34:43,324 --> 01:34:44,837
I'm all right, I'm all right.

1257
01:34:46,604 --> 01:34:47,832
Speak to him, David.

1258
01:34:49,044 --> 01:34:50,762
Tell him we came, just like he asked.

1259
01:34:50,924 --> 01:34:52,039
Ask where they're from.

1260
01:34:52,644 --> 01:34:53,474
What are you doing?

1261
01:34:53,644 --> 01:34:55,236
Ask him what's in his cargo.

1262
01:34:55,404 --> 01:34:56,200
It killed his people.

1263
01:34:56,364 --> 01:34:57,433
Shaw, enough.

1264
01:34:57,724 --> 01:34:59,396
- David.
- You made it here...

1265
01:34:59,884 --> 01:35:02,444
...and it was meant for us. Why?

1266
01:35:02,604 --> 01:35:04,356
Enough. For God's sake, shut her up.

1267
01:35:06,444 --> 01:35:07,513
I need to know why!

1268
01:35:07,684 --> 01:35:09,322
What did we do wrong? Why do you...

1269
01:35:09,484 --> 01:35:10,883
- ...hate us?
- She opens her...

1270
01:35:11,044 --> 01:35:12,033
...mouth again, shoot her.

1271
01:35:12,204 --> 01:35:14,035
David, continue. Tell him why I came.

1272
01:35:34,084 --> 01:35:34,834
No!

1273
01:35:40,684 --> 01:35:41,639
Ford! Move!

1274
01:36:00,004 --> 01:36:03,599
There's nothing.

1275
01:36:08,524 --> 01:36:10,242
I know.

1276
01:36:10,924 --> 01:36:13,757
Have a good journey, Mr. Weyland.

1277
01:36:19,964 --> 01:36:21,477
Time to go home.

1278
01:36:34,364 --> 01:36:37,322
Mr. Chance, take us home.

1279
01:37:47,364 --> 01:37:48,194
Oh, no!

1280
01:37:55,724 --> 01:37:56,679
Hey, cap.

1281
01:37:57,204 --> 01:37:58,239
What the hell was that?

1282
01:38:40,684 --> 01:38:41,434
Prometheus!

1283
01:38:41,924 --> 01:38:42,913
Come in!

1284
01:38:43,724 --> 01:38:44,918
Shaw, is that you?

1285
01:38:45,084 --> 01:38:45,800
Copy.

1286
01:38:45,964 --> 01:38:46,601
Janek...

1287
01:38:46,764 --> 01:38:47,719
...listen to me.

1288
01:38:48,604 --> 01:38:49,798
This ship is taking off!

1289
01:38:49,964 --> 01:38:51,522
- What?
- What is she talking about?

1290
01:38:51,684 --> 01:38:53,163
You can't let it leave!

1291
01:38:53,444 --> 01:38:54,433
You have to stop it!

1292
01:38:54,764 --> 01:38:57,278
We're not stopping anything, Shaw.
We're going home.

1293
01:38:57,764 --> 01:38:59,720
Janek, if you don't stop it...

1294
01:38:59,884 --> 01:39:01,636
...there won't be any home to go back to.

1295
01:39:03,564 --> 01:39:06,078
It's carrying death, and it's headed for Earth.

1296
01:39:06,364 --> 01:39:08,639
- Shaw, this is not a warship.
- I know.

1297
01:39:08,804 --> 01:39:09,554
Let's go.

1298
01:39:09,724 --> 01:39:10,918
I know that.

1299
01:39:11,564 --> 01:39:13,282
But you must do it.

1300
01:39:13,804 --> 01:39:15,396
Captain, let's go!

1301
01:39:15,564 --> 01:39:17,555
Janek, please believe me! Please!

1302
01:39:32,604 --> 01:39:34,913
I told you to get this ship going.

1303
01:39:35,084 --> 01:39:35,880
Mr. Ravel.

1304
01:39:36,044 --> 01:39:37,318
Warm up the ion propulsion.

1305
01:39:37,644 --> 01:39:39,236
- What are you talking about?
- Sir.

1306
01:39:39,404 --> 01:39:40,996
Burning ion in the atmosphere--

1307
01:39:41,164 --> 01:39:44,122
- Turns us into a bullet. That's the point.
- What are you doing?

1308
01:39:44,284 --> 01:39:45,956
This is my ship. I'm telling you...

1309
01:39:46,124 --> 01:39:47,159
...to take us home!

1310
01:39:47,324 --> 01:39:48,757
Vickers, I'll eject your module onto...

1311
01:39:48,924 --> 01:39:50,596
...that surface. Two years of life.

1312
01:39:50,764 --> 01:39:52,675
You want it, or you want to stay with me?

1313
01:39:53,564 --> 01:39:54,838
You got 40 seconds to get...

1314
01:39:55,004 --> 01:39:55,959
...to the escape pod.

1315
01:39:56,124 --> 01:39:57,159
You're crazy.

1316
01:39:57,324 --> 01:39:58,040
Gentlemen...

1317
01:39:58,604 --> 01:40:00,196
...I can handle this myself.

1318
01:40:00,684 --> 01:40:02,356
Feel free to join Miss Vickers.

1319
01:40:03,204 --> 01:40:04,523
All due respect, captain.

1320
01:40:04,684 --> 01:40:07,801
You're a shit pilot and you're gonna
need all the help you can get.

1321
01:40:23,404 --> 01:40:27,397
Well, if you can't be with the one you love

1322
01:40:27,564 --> 01:40:29,714
If you think this means the bet's off...

1323
01:40:31,004 --> 01:40:32,198
...you're wrong.

1324
01:40:33,764 --> 01:40:36,039
Why don't you pay me on the other side?

1325
01:40:36,204 --> 01:40:38,195
All right, get us as close as we can.

1326
01:40:38,364 --> 01:40:40,195
Only got one shot at this.

1327
01:40:52,764 --> 01:40:53,401
Lifeboats away!

1328
01:40:58,444 --> 01:40:59,354
Twenty seconds...

1329
01:40:59,524 --> 01:41:00,479
...to evacuate.

1330
01:41:08,044 --> 01:41:09,762
- Countdown initiated.
- lon propulsion...

1331
01:41:09,924 --> 01:41:10,595
...is online.

1332
01:41:10,964 --> 01:41:11,635
Ten.

1333
01:41:12,044 --> 01:41:12,681
Nine.

1334
01:41:12,964 --> 01:41:13,794
Come on!

1335
01:41:13,964 --> 01:41:14,919
Eight.

1336
01:41:26,684 --> 01:41:27,958
- Three.
- Let's do this.

1337
01:41:28,124 --> 01:41:28,954
Two.

1338
01:41:32,164 --> 01:41:32,994
Impact imminent.

1339
01:41:33,164 --> 01:41:34,517
Hands off!

1340
01:42:09,884 --> 01:42:10,600
Oh, God.

1341
01:42:56,204 --> 01:42:57,159
No. No.

1342
01:42:57,324 --> 01:42:58,359
No! No! No!

1343
01:43:13,964 --> 01:43:14,999
Oh, God.

1344
01:43:30,764 --> 01:43:33,915
Warning: You have two minutes
of oxygen remaining.

1345
01:44:20,364 --> 01:44:24,073
Warning: You have 30 seconds
of oxygen remaining.

1346
01:44:37,084 --> 01:44:38,153
Airlock sealed.

1347
01:44:39,724 --> 01:44:42,113
Oxygen levels now stabilizing.

1348
01:45:56,884 --> 01:45:58,761
Elizabeth, are you there?

1349
01:45:59,244 --> 01:46:00,393
This is David.

1350
01:46:01,564 --> 01:46:03,953
Yeah. Yeah. Yeah, I'm here.

1351
01:46:04,244 --> 01:46:06,439
You need to get out immediately.

1352
01:46:06,724 --> 01:46:08,555
He's coming for you.

1353
01:46:08,764 --> 01:46:09,753
Who's coming?

1354
01:46:10,284 --> 01:46:11,353
Airlock breach.

1355
01:46:19,604 --> 01:46:20,593
Die!

1356
01:47:42,644 --> 01:47:44,999
I'm so sorry.

1357
01:47:46,404 --> 01:47:48,201
Oh, God.

1358
01:47:48,804 --> 01:47:50,123
I'm sorry.

1359
01:47:50,284 --> 01:47:53,594
I'm sorry, Charlie, I can't do it.

1360
01:47:53,764 --> 01:47:56,801
I can't do it anymore.

1361
01:48:00,044 --> 01:48:01,477
Elizabeth.

1362
01:48:03,364 --> 01:48:04,513
Are you there?

1363
01:48:08,844 --> 01:48:10,277
Dr. Shaw...

1364
01:48:10,964 --> 01:48:12,192
...can you hear me?

1365
01:48:13,444 --> 01:48:14,638
Yes.

1366
01:48:16,044 --> 01:48:18,114
Yes, I can hear you.

1367
01:48:18,644 --> 01:48:20,441
I was afraid you were dead.

1368
01:48:22,124 --> 01:48:24,957
You have no idea what afraid is.

1369
01:48:25,764 --> 01:48:28,437
I know we've had our differences...

1370
01:48:29,804 --> 01:48:31,203
...but, please...

1371
01:48:32,084 --> 01:48:34,279
...I need to ask you for your help.

1372
01:48:34,444 --> 01:48:36,878
Why the hell would I help you?

1373
01:48:38,564 --> 01:48:42,273
Because, without me,
you'll never leave this place.

1374
01:48:42,924 --> 01:48:45,961
Neither one of us is leaving this place.

1375
01:48:46,404 --> 01:48:48,360
It's not the only ship.

1376
01:48:50,164 --> 01:48:52,155
There are many others.

1377
01:48:53,484 --> 01:48:54,758
I can operate them.

1378
01:49:03,564 --> 01:49:04,917
Dr. Shaw?

1379
01:49:17,164 --> 01:49:18,358
Dr. Shaw!

1380
01:49:19,724 --> 01:49:20,839
Over here.

1381
01:49:26,324 --> 01:49:28,201
Where is my cross?

1382
01:49:28,684 --> 01:49:30,481
The pouch in my utility belt.

1383
01:49:48,484 --> 01:49:50,236
Even after all this...

1384
01:49:50,404 --> 01:49:52,360
...you still believe, don't you?

1385
01:49:53,164 --> 01:49:56,042
You said you could
understand their navigation...

1386
01:49:56,564 --> 01:49:57,758
...use their maps.

1387
01:49:59,684 --> 01:50:01,322
Yes, of course.

1388
01:50:01,484 --> 01:50:03,714
Once we get
to one of their other ships...

1389
01:50:03,884 --> 01:50:06,876
...finding a path to Earth
should be relatively straightforward.

1390
01:50:07,564 --> 01:50:10,397
I don't want to go back
to where we came from.

1391
01:50:12,164 --> 01:50:14,724
I want to go where they came from.

1392
01:50:16,044 --> 01:50:18,353
Do you think you can do that, David?

1393
01:50:22,084 --> 01:50:23,233
Yes.

1394
01:50:23,844 --> 01:50:25,641
I believe I can.

1395
01:50:34,604 --> 01:50:37,118
May I ask what you hope to achieve
by going there?

1396
01:50:37,764 --> 01:50:39,755
They created us.

1397
01:50:39,964 --> 01:50:41,443
Then they tried to kill us.

1398
01:50:41,964 --> 01:50:43,795
They changed their minds.

1399
01:50:45,324 --> 01:50:46,916
I deserve to know why.

1400
01:50:49,004 --> 01:50:50,562
The answer is irrelevant.

1401
01:50:51,564 --> 01:50:53,759
Does it matter why
they changed their minds?

1402
01:50:54,444 --> 01:50:55,559
Yes.

1403
01:50:56,844 --> 01:50:58,436
Yes, it does.

1404
01:50:59,404 --> 01:51:00,519
I don't understand.

1405
01:51:01,964 --> 01:51:03,033
Well...

1406
01:51:05,004 --> 01:51:07,916
...I guess that's because
I'm a human being...

1407
01:51:08,084 --> 01:51:09,483
...and you're a robot.

1408
01:51:18,924 --> 01:51:19,834
I'm sorry.

1409
01:51:20,004 --> 01:51:21,153
It's quite all right.

1410
01:51:35,724 --> 01:51:38,397
Final report of the vessel Prometheus.

1411
01:51:38,564 --> 01:51:39,474
The ship and her...

1412
01:51:39,644 --> 01:51:41,680
...entire crew are gone.

1413
01:51:41,884 --> 01:51:43,681
If you're receiving this transmission...

1414
01:51:43,844 --> 01:51:47,075
...make no attempt
to come to its point of origin.

1415
01:51:47,244 --> 01:51:51,283
There is only death here now,
and I'm leaving it behind.

1416
01:51:52,324 --> 01:51:54,042
It is New Year's Day...

1417
01:51:54,204 --> 01:51:57,116
...the year of our Lord, 2094.

1418
01:51:58,004 --> 01:52:00,393
My name is Elizabeth Shaw...

1419
01:52:00,604 --> 01:52:03,402
...the last survivor of the Prometheus.

1420
01:52:03,884 --> 01:52:06,273
And I am still searching.
